freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Bowel pressure, hypersensitivity of skin on my fingertips, similar to what I have experienced when I had a fever.  Temperature was only 98.5.  Hot beverages, a 3-hour nap and an extra sweater helped and I'm feeling much better now.
None today so far, but the past several evenings, I have had a small, itchy rash on my forearm for a few hours and treated it with cortisone cream.   I doubt that it's associated with the vaccine.
